    <txttips>
        <txttip left="36" top="252" right="1258" bottom="516" content="Instructions:&#x0D;&#x0A;1. Start-up the topology&#x0D;&#x0A;2. Double click the PC and go to the console tab.&#x0D;&#x0A;3. Complete basic configurations of the router. Device name(name should be Firstname - Router), IP address for each &#x0D;&#x0A;   interface based on;&#x0D;&#x0A;   GigabitEthernet0/0/1 - 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0&#x0D;&#x0A;   GigabitEthernet0/0/2 - 192.168.2.1 255.255.255.0&#x0D;&#x0A;   GigabitEthernet0/0/3 - 192.168.3.1 255.255.255.0&#x0D;&#x0A;4. Use the command &apos;display ip interface brief&apos; to confirm the ip address configurations&#x0D;&#x0A;5. run &apos;display current-configuration&apos; to see all the other configurations on the Router.&#x0D;&#x0A;6. run &apos;save&apos; to save the router configurations. Don&apos;t forget to comfirm saving at the prompt.&#x0D;&#x0A;7. Save the complete work as &apos;Firstname-UserID-Lab4&apos; and zip the resulting folder. Upload the zip to the lms" fontname="Consolas" fontstyle="0" editsize="140" txtcolor="-16777216" txtbkcolor="-2044184" charset="1" />
    </txttips>
